title: For Sale/Trade:  Century C93 (HK93 Clone)
postcontent: *Please do not offer anything outside of the noted trade section or ask if I will ship the items. The listing will be adjusted accordingly if I change either aspects.*Face to face sales only.The rifle functions and fires perfectly. It comes with an all matching bolt carrier from a Malaysian parts kit. The sights are appropriately aligned and it will seat a factory original claw mount without any issues. Cocking the rifle is not a problem by any means. outside of a few welds, it is an overall excellent build. The slight overweld is at the mag well, it is nothing major and does not hinder the insertion or release of magazines. The other place that would be noted from the original is the eyebolt. Rather than have the end crushed to hold it was welded over. This does not inhibit form or function, but if looking to being as close to original this is not. The receiver itself does not fit the hk93 design as it utilizes the G3 style of magwell support. The bolt gap is .018". It will not completely fit the .019", but slides in the .018" gauge with ease. The rifle is parkerized with minor finish wear from the original carry handle, as well as when I added a trunnion clasped bipod. The flash hider, unlike the initial run, can be removed. There is no solder used to keep it attached to the barrel. Like most of the C93's it does not have a paddle mag release but does have the bayonet adapter installed. The receiver is manufactured by Hesse. The serial number is C9315XXX. I have fired (480) rounds of brass cased ammunition. All of which was Remington .223. There were (200) rounds of Wolf, and (280) rounds of Armscor. Using the original 40 round mag that was dented at the back there have been zero failures of any kind. I did check to see if steel 30 rounds will fit and lock in place. They will go in, but trying to remove them is a bit of a chore. The mag release stiffens and is impossible to push with your index finger from the pistol grip and clamps to the magazines for dear life. I would recommend either using strictly 40 rounders, shortening the shelf of the mag catch, or replacing the mag catch with a new one. On my other C93 the 30 rounders fit and release without a problem, but the mag catch was more worn than this one. I will adjust the price based on the setup you choose. Feel free to look at my other listing of HK parts to determine what is best suited for you. For Barreled receiver (excludes bolt carrier, magazine, handguard, stock, and carry handle) $250. For receiver w/ bolt carrier only, the price is $500. I will also sell complete rifle without the magazine for $575. The third image is of items I do own, but is meant as a representation of the possibilities to which one can set up the rifle.
